ciscoLwappMdnsMIB.name: ciscoLwappMdnsMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoLwappMdnsMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Customer Service Postal: 170 West Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS Email: cs-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoLwappMdnsMIB.description: Multicast DNS (mDNS) is a way of using familiar Domain Name System (DNS) programming interfaces, packet formats and operating, without configuring a conventional DNS server. It is useful in small networks without a DNS server, but can also work in environments beside a DNS server. mDNS functionality is provided using IP multicast over User Datagram Protocol (UDP). The mDNS protocol is used by Apple's Bonjour, Linux Avahi, and Oracle Grid Naming Service (GNS) service discovery systems. GLOSSARY Access Point ( AP ) An entity that contains an 802.11 medium access control ( MAC ) and physical layer ( PHY ) interface and provides access to the distribution services via the wireless medium for associated clients. LWAPP APs encapsulate all the 802.11 frames in LWAPP frames and sends it to the controller to which it is logically connected to. Central Controller ( CC ) The central entity that terminates the LWAPP protocol tunnel from the LWAPP APs. Throughout this MIB, this entity also referred to as 'controller'. Light Weight Access Point Protocol ( LWAPP ) This is a generic protocol that defines the communication between the Access Points and the controllers. Mobile Node ( MN ) A roaming 802.11 wireless device in a wireless network associated with an access point. AVC - Application Visiblity and Control. The client application or protocol statistics and control.

clMdnsSnoopingEnabled.name: clMdnsSnoopingEnabled
clMdnsSnoopingEnabled.description: This object specifies whether Mdns Snooping is enabled or disabled on the controller. A value of 'true' specifies that Mdns Snooping is enabled and a value of 'false' specifies that Mdns Snooping is disabled on the controller.

clMdnsQueryInterval.name: clMdnsQueryInterval
clMdnsQueryInterval.description: This object specifies the Mdns query interval, in minutes. To set this value, clMdnsSnoopingEnabled must be set to True.

clMdnsMasterServiceTable.name: clMdnsMasterServiceTable
clMdnsMasterServiceTable.description: This table represents the configuration of all the Mdns Services supported on the Wireless LAN Controller(WLC).

clMdnsMasterServiceEntry.name: clMdnsMasterServiceEntry
clMdnsMasterServiceEntry.description: This represents an entry in the clMdnsMasterServiceTable. Each entry corresponds to a service, indicated by clMdnsServiceName.

clMdnsServiceName.name: clMdnsServiceName
clMdnsServiceName.description: This object represents the name of the mdns service added on the controller.

clMdnsServiceString.name: clMdnsServiceString
clMdnsServiceString.description: This object represents the service string defined for the mdns service added on the controller.

clMdnsServiceQueryStatus.name: clMdnsServiceQueryStatus
clMdnsServiceQueryStatus.description: This object indicates whether the service represented by clMdnsServiceName, will be queried by the WLC.

clMdnsServiceRowStatus.name: clMdnsServiceRowStatus
clMdnsServiceRowStatus.description: This object is used to add or delete entries in clMdnsMasterServiceTable

clMdnsProfileTable.name: clMdnsProfileTable
clMdnsProfileTable.description: This table represents the configuration of all the Mdns profiles on the Wireless LAN Controller(WLC).

clMdnsProfileEntry.name: clMdnsProfileEntry
clMdnsProfileEntry.description: This represents an entry in the clMdnsProfileTable. Each entry corresponds to a mdns profiles, indicated by clMdnsProfileName.

clMdnsProfileName.name: clMdnsProfileName
clMdnsProfileName.description: This object represents the name of the mdns profile added on the controller.

clMdnsProfileRowStatus.name: clMdnsProfileRowStatus
clMdnsProfileRowStatus.description: This object is used to add or delete entries in clMdnsProfileTable

clMdnsProfileWlanCount.name: clMdnsProfileWlanCount
clMdnsProfileWlanCount.description: This object specifies the number of WLANs on which the profile is attached.

clMdnsProfileInterfaceCount.name: clMdnsProfileInterfaceCount
clMdnsProfileInterfaceCount.description: This object specifies the number of Interfaces on which the profile is attached.

clMdnsProfileInterfaceGrpCount.name: clMdnsProfileInterfaceGrpCount
clMdnsProfileInterfaceGrpCount.description: This object specifies the number of Inteface groups on which the profile is attached.

clMdnsProfileServiceTable.name: clMdnsProfileServiceTable
clMdnsProfileServiceTable.description: This table represents the configuration of all the Services added to Mdns profiles on the Wireless LAN Controller(WLC).

clMdnsProfileServiceEntry.name: clMdnsProfileServiceEntry
clMdnsProfileServiceEntry.description: This represents an entry in the clMdnsProfileServiceTable. Each entry corresponds to a service in the mdns profile.

clMdnsProfileServiceRowStatus.name: clMdnsProfileServiceRowStatus
clMdnsProfileServiceRowStatus.description: This object is used to add or delete entries in clMdnsProfileServiceTable.

clMdnsServiceProviderTable.name: clMdnsServiceProviderTable
clMdnsServiceProviderTable.description: This table represents the list of all the Service providers who have advertised Mdns services on the Wireless LAN Controller(WLC).

clMdnsServiceProviderEntry.name: clMdnsServiceProviderEntry
clMdnsServiceProviderEntry.description: This represents an entry in the clMdnsServiceProviderTable. Each entry corresponds to a service Povider.

clMdnsServiceProviderIndex.name: clMdnsServiceProviderIndex
clMdnsServiceProviderIndex.description: This object specifies a unique index assigned by the wireless controller when the service provider entry is added.

clMdnsServiceProviderMacAddress.name: clMdnsServiceProviderMacAddress
clMdnsServiceProviderMacAddress.description: This object specifies the hardware address of the service provider machine.

clMdnsServiceProviderName.name: clMdnsServiceProviderName
clMdnsServiceProviderName.description: This object specifies the hostname assigned to the service provider machine.

clMdnsServiceProviderVlan.name: clMdnsServiceProviderVlan
clMdnsServiceProviderVlan.description: This object specifies the VLAN on which the service provider is operating.

clMdnsServiceProviderType.name: clMdnsServiceProviderType
clMdnsServiceProviderType.description: This object specifies whether the the service provider is operating in a wired or wireless network.

clMdnsServiceProviderTtl.name: clMdnsServiceProviderTtl
clMdnsServiceProviderTtl.description: This object specifies the TTL (time to live) value in secondes, assigned when the service provider entry is added. The entry will be removed from the control on expiry of this.

clMdnsServiceProviderTimeLeft.name: clMdnsServiceProviderTimeLeft
clMdnsServiceProviderTimeLeft.description: This object specifies the Time left before the entry is removed from the controller.

clMdnsDnipTable.name: clMdnsDnipTable
clMdnsDnipTable.description: This table represents the list of all the Domain Name IP entries on the Wireless LAN Controller(WLC). The entries are learnt from the mDNS advertisements

clMdnsDnipEntry.name: clMdnsDnipEntry
clMdnsDnipEntry.description: This represents an entry in the clMdnsDnipTable. Each entry corresponds to a Domain Name IP entry.

clMdnsDomainName.name: clMdnsDomainName
clMdnsDomainName.description: This object specifies the domain name added on the controller.

clMdnsDomainMacAddress.name: clMdnsDomainMacAddress
clMdnsDomainMacAddress.description: This object specifies the hardware address of the service provider machine.

clMdnsDomainIpAddressType.name: clMdnsDomainIpAddressType
clMdnsDomainIpAddressType.description: This object specifies the IP address type assigned to the domain.

clMdnsDomainIpAddress.name: clMdnsDomainIpAddress
clMdnsDomainIpAddress.description: This object specifies the IP address assigned to the domain.

clMdnsDomainVlan.name: clMdnsDomainVlan
clMdnsDomainVlan.description: This object specifies the VLAN on which the domain is operating.

clMdnsDomainType.name: clMdnsDomainType
clMdnsDomainType.description: This object specifies whether the the Domain name IP entry is a wired, wireless or wired-guest host.

clMdnsDomainEntryTtl.name: clMdnsDomainEntryTtl
clMdnsDomainEntryTtl.description: This object specifies the TTL (time to live) value in secondes, assigned when the domain entry is added. The entry will be removed from the control on expiry of this.

clMdnsDomainEntryTimeLeft.name: clMdnsDomainEntryTimeLeft
clMdnsDomainEntryTimeLeft.description: This object specifies the Time left before the entry is removed from the controller.

cLMdnsServiceGroupTable.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupTable
cLMdnsServiceGroupTable.description: The table contains the Service group information. Service group is group of devices and Location. Rows are added or deleted by explicit management actions initiated by the user from a network management station through the cLMdnsServiceGroupRowStatus object.

cLMdnsServiceGroupName.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupName
cLMdnsServiceGroupName.description: This object defines name of the group and it is unique

cLMdnsServiceGroupDescription.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupDescription
cLMdnsServiceGroupDescription.description: This object defines the description of the group name

cLMdnsServiceGroupRowStatus.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupRowStatus
cLMdnsServiceGroupRowStatus.description: Row Status for creation/deletion of a particular venue entry in the table.

cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacTable.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacTable
cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacTable.description: The table contains set of Devices and device group map to a service group. Rows are added or deleted by explicit management actions initiated by the user from a network management station through the cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacRowStatus object.

cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMac.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMac
cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMac.description: This object defines the device MAC of the device which is grouped in service group.

cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceName.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceName
cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceName.description: This object defines the unique device name of the device.

cLMdnsServiceGroupLocationName.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupLocationName
cLMdnsServiceGroupLocationName.description: This object defines the location of the device.

cLMdnsServiceGroupLocationType.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupLocationType
cLMdnsServiceGroupLocationType.description: This object list the location type provided by the service provider (device).

cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacRowStatus.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacRowStatus
cLMdnsServiceGroupDeviceMacRowStatus.description: Row Status for creation/deletion of a particular venue entry in the table.

cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleTable.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleTable
cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleTable.description: This table is for the mapping Service group to a Rule or set of rules. Rows are added or deleted by explicit management actions initiated by the user from a network management station through the cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleRowStatus object.

cLMdnsRuleName.name: cLMdnsRuleName
cLMdnsRuleName.description: This object uniquely identifies a Rule which is Added to a Rule table.

cLMdnsRuleRole.name: cLMdnsRuleRole
cLMdnsRuleRole.description: This object defines the set of roles apply to the Service group.

cLMdnsRuleUserId.name: cLMdnsRuleUserId
cLMdnsRuleUserId.description: This object defines the set of userIds apply to the service group.

cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleRowStatus.name: cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleRowStatus
cLMdnsServiceGroupRuleRowStatus.description: Row Status for creation/deletion of a particular venue entry in the table.

ciscoLwappMdnsMIBCompliance.name: ciscoLwappMdnsMIBCompliance
ciscoLwappMdnsMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the SNMP entities that implement the ciscoLwappMdnsMIB module.

cLMdnsConfigGroup.name: cLMdnsConfigGroup
cLMdnsConfigGroup.description: This is a collection of objects which can be used to control Mdns parameters.

cLMdnsMonitorGroup.name: cLMdnsMonitorGroup
cLMdnsMonitorGroup.description: This is a collection of objects which can be used to monitor Mdns parameters.
